# Samples and Aspire AppHost

- Prefer repo guidance in [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) and [docs/evaluation-technical-improvements.md](../../docs/evaluation-technical-improvements.md) for loop models (`Simulator` vs Raylib window), `NullInputSource` (avoid duplicate global hooks), and audio (`SilentAudioPlayer` off Windows).
- **Aspire**: the AppHost under `dev/` orchestrates sample **executables** for local dev. It is not a substitute for documenting the engine’s two execution models.
- **Run one windowed sample at a time** from the dashboard when using Raylib/MonoGame; multiple full-screen or competing GL contexts are a common footgun.
- **CI**: AppHost and samples are **compile-tested** in the solution build; do not assume headless Linux CI can launch interactive windows.
- Keep sample logging teachable: avoid `Console.WriteLine` every frame unless gated behind a debug flag (see technical evaluation).
